1) ifconfig - display network interface info
2) ping - send ICMP echo requests to a host : ping google.com
3) netstat - display n/w connections and stats : netstat -tuln (show all listening to TCP & UDP connections)
4) ss - display n/w socket info : ss -tuln (show all listening to TCP and UDP connections)
5) ssh - securely connect to a remore server : ssh user@hostname
6) scp - securely copy files between hosts : scp file.txt user@hostname:/path/to/destination
7) wget - download files from the web : wget http://example.com/file.txt
8) curl - transfer data to or from a server : curl http://example.om
